# Spec: Phase 6 — Dev Execution Loop + Infrastructure + Agents + Skills + UI Quality

## Goal
Implement 23 improvements sourced from the awesome-claude-plugins research (6 deep-research reports). Upgrades span the full BrickLayer stack: dev execution loop reliability, infrastructure hooks, new specialist agents, new skills, and UI quality gates.

## Success Criteria
- [ ] fix-implementer uses commit-before-verify+revert pattern (no silent failures)
- [ ] /build uses Guard/Verify split (full suite vs task metric)
- [ ] spec-reviewer agent exists and is wired into /build between developer and code-reviewer
- [ ] /debug skill exists as an 8-step loop (not one-shot)
- [ ] /aside skill exists (freeze task, read-only answer, resume)
- [ ] masonry-pre-compact.js saves full build/campaign state before compaction
- [ ] masonry-config-protection.js blocks writes to lint config sections
- [ ] masonry-block-no-verify.js blocks --no-verify and --force in Bash commands
- [ ] masonry-context-monitor.js detects semantic degradation via Ollama cosine similarity
- [ ] 5 new agents exist in both ~/.claude/agents/ and template/.claude/agents/ and masonry/agent_registry.yml
- [ ] 7 new skills exist in ~/.claude/skills/
- [ ] uiux-master has 7-point slop gate and domain exploration forcing function
- [ ] masonry/tests/test_wiring_completeness.py still passes after all changes

