## Tasks

- [ ] **Task 1** — Upgrade fix-implementer: commit-before-verify+revert pattern
  **Files:** `~/.claude/agents/fix-implementer.md`, `template/.claude/agents/fix-implementer.md`
  **What to build:** After each fix attempt, commit with `experiment: fix attempt N` prefix, run the Guard (full test suite) and Verify (task-specific metric). If Guard fails: `git revert HEAD --no-edit` and try next approach. If Guard passes but Verify fails: keep the commit but log "metric not improved" and escalate. Max 3 attempts before BLOCKED. This prevents silent regression creep and makes every fix auditable.
  **Tests required:** Read the agent file and verify the commit-before-verify+revert workflow is documented with the `experiment:` prefix, Guard/Verify split, and 3-attempt cap.

- [ ] **Task 2** — Add Guard/Verify split to /build skill
  **Files:** `~/.claude/skills/build/SKILL.md`
  **What to build:** In the Per-Task Loop Step 4 (Validate), split into two checks: Guard = full test suite (did anything break?), Verify = task-specific metric (did this task's goal improve?). Guard failing = spawn fix agent. Guard passes but Verify fails = log warning, continue. Document that Guard uses `-q --tb=short` and Verify uses the test file for that specific task. Add to Step 6 (Commit): commit message should use `feat:` for Guard+Verify pass, `experiment:` for Guard-pass-only commits.
  **Tests required:** Read the skill file and verify Guard/Verify split is documented with distinct behaviors for each outcome.

- [ ] **Task 3** — Create spec-reviewer agent
  **Files:** `~/.claude/agents/spec-reviewer.md`, `template/.claude/agents/spec-reviewer.md`, `masonry/agent_registry.yml`
  **What to build:** A new agent that sits between developer and code-reviewer in the /build pipeline. Reads the original spec task description + the files changed by the developer agent. Returns one of: COMPLIANT (implementation matches spec), OVER_BUILT (more than asked), UNDER_BUILT (less than asked), SCOPE_DRIFT (different direction than spec). Agent is read-only — no code changes. Structured output block: `## Spec Review\n**Verdict:** COMPLIANT|OVER_BUILT|UNDER_BUILT|SCOPE_DRIFT\n**Evidence:** ...\n**Required action:** ...`
  **Tests required:** Both agent files exist. Registry entry exists in agent_registry.yml with tier: draft.

- [ ] **Task 4** — Wire spec-reviewer into /build skill [depends:3]
  **Files:** `~/.claude/skills/build/SKILL.md`
  **What to build:** After Step 3 (developer returns) and before Step 5 (code-reviewer), add Step 4a — spec-reviewer gate. Spawn spec-reviewer with task description + files changed. If OVER_BUILT/UNDER_BUILT/SCOPE_DRIFT: spawn developer with feedback (1 correction cycle) before proceeding to code-reviewer. If COMPLIANT: proceed directly. Skip for [mode:security], [mode:architect], [mode:review-only] tasks.
  **Tests required:** Read the skill file and verify spec-reviewer gate is in the pipeline between developer and code-reviewer with the skip conditions listed.

- [ ] **Task 5** — Create /debug skill as a loop
  **Files:** `~/.claude/skills/debug/SKILL.md`
  **What to build:** A skill that runs diagnosis as a structured 8-step loop: (1) Binary search, (2) Differential, (3) Minimal repro, (4) Forward trace, (5) Pattern search, (6) Backward trace, (7) Rubber duck, (8) Hypothesis log. Loop continues until root cause found or all 8 exhausted. On exhaustion: write DIAGNOSIS_FAILED.md and escalate to user. Invoked as `/debug <error description or file>`.
  **Tests required:** Skill file exists. Documents all 8 techniques with descriptions. Has loop structure with escalation condition.

- [ ] **Task 6** — Create /aside skill
