- [ ] **Task 8** — Create masonry-config-protection.js hook
  **Files:** `masonry/src/hooks/masonry-config-protection.js`, `~/.claude/settings.json`
  **What to build:** PreToolUse Write|Edit hook blocking writes to lint config sections. Protected: `.eslintrc*`, `.prettierrc*`, `prettier.config.*`, `ruff.toml`, `[tool.ruff]` in pyproject.toml, `[tool.black]` in pyproject.toml. On block: exit code 2, print `[masonry-config-protection] BLOCKED: Write to lint config requires explicit override. Add # LINT_CONFIG_OVERRIDE to your message to proceed.` If user message contains `LINT_CONFIG_OVERRIDE`: allow. Wire in settings.json PreToolUse Write|Edit with timeout: 3, continueOnError: false.
  **Tests required:** Hook file exists. Settings.json has the hook wired in PreToolUse Write|Edit section.

- [ ] **Task 9** — Create masonry-block-no-verify.js hook
  **Files:** `masonry/src/hooks/masonry-block-no-verify.js`, `~/.claude/settings.json`
  **What to build:** PreToolUse Bash hook blocking dangerous git flags. Blocked: `--no-verify` in any git command, `--force` on `git push`, `-f` on `git push`. Allow `--force-with-lease`. On block: exit code 2, print `[masonry-block-no-verify] BLOCKED: {pattern} bypasses safety checks. Fix the underlying issue instead.` Wire in settings.json PreToolUse Bash BEFORE masonry-approver with timeout: 3, continueOnError: false.
  **Tests required:** Hook file exists. Settings.json has the hook wired before masonry-approver. Logic distinguishes git push --force vs other --force usages.

- [ ] **Task 10** — Extend masonry-context-monitor.js: semantic degradation detection
  **Files:** `masonry/src/hooks/masonry-context-monitor.js`
  **What to build:** Read the existing hook first. Add semantic degradation check at Stop time using Ollama nomic-embed-text embeddings (OLLAMA_HOST env or http://100.70.195.84:11434). 4 degradation patterns via cosine similarity: (1) Lost-in-middle — recent vs first assistant message similarity < 0.3, (2) Poisoning — consecutive similarity drop > 0.5, (3) Distraction — recent messages unrelated to progress.json task, (4) Clash — two recent messages similarity < 0.1. On detection: print `[masonry-context-monitor] WARNING: Semantic degradation detected — {pattern}. Consider /compact.` Ollama unreachable: skip silently.
  **Tests required:** Read the hook and verify 4 degradation patterns with thresholds and graceful Ollama failure handling are present.

- [ ] **Task 11** [phase_end:agents] — Create 5 new specialist agents
  **Files:** `~/.claude/agents/verification-analyst.md`, `~/.claude/agents/mcp-developer.md`, `~/.claude/agents/chaos-engineer.md`, `~/.claude/agents/penetration-tester.md`, `~/.claude/agents/scientific-literature-researcher.md`, plus `template/.claude/agents/` copies and `masonry/agent_registry.yml` entries
  **What to build:**
  1. **verification-analyst** — Mandatory 6-gate verification for security/research findings: Process, Reachability, Real Impact, PoC, Math Bounds, Environment. Returns VERIFIED|UNVERIFIED|INCONCLUSIVE with gate-by-gate evidence. Includes 13-item Devil's Advocate checklist. Notes LLM-bias warning ("LLMs are biased toward seeing bugs and overrating severity").
  2. **mcp-developer** — MCP server specialist. Knows MCP SDK, tool schema design, stdio/SSE transport, error handling. Scaffolds new servers, adds tools to existing ones, writes tests with the MCP test client.
  3. **chaos-engineer** — Controlled failure injection: service failure, network partition, resource exhaustion, clock skew, slow dependencies. Proposes experiments with blast radius analysis. Read-only default; execution requires explicit user approval.
  4. **penetration-tester** — Security testing with required authorization context. Tests: auth bypass, injection, privilege escalation, exposed secrets, SSRF, insecure deserialization. Returns CVSS-scored findings. Refuses without authorization context in prompt.
  5. **scientific-literature-researcher** — Grounds findings in peer-reviewed literature. Searches arXiv, Semantic Scholar, PubMed. Extracts citation, abstract, key claims, methodology, sample size, effect size, CIs. Flags: predatory journals, unreviewed preprints, industry-funded studies.
  All 5: frontmatter with name/description, entries in agent_registry.yml with tier: "draft".
  **Tests required:** All 10 agent files exist (5 × 2 paths). All 5 entries in agent_registry.yml.

